Python Implementation
=====================

A pure-Python port of the Perl module is provided in ``genomeid.py``.
The Python output IDs match the Perl implementation byte-for-byte for
the same inputs.

DEPENDENCIES (Python)

    pip install pysam

USAGE

    from genomeid import generate_id

    # From a plain VCF file
    gid = generate_id(file='sample.vcf', type='vcf', hg='hg38')
    print(gid)   # e.g. "/gAAAAAAAABB"  (12-char base64 without sex markers)

    # From a bgzip+tabix-indexed VCF (uses pysam.TabixFile internally)
    gid = generate_id(file='sample.vcf.gz', type='tbi', hg='hg38', sex=True)
    print(gid)   # 20-char base64 (includes X/Y marker bits)

    # From a BAM file (uses pysam.AlignmentFile + pileup)
    gid = generate_id(file='sample.bam', type='bam', hg='hg38', sex=True)
    print(gid)

    # Multi-sample VCF: select sample by name
    gid = generate_id(file='cohort.vcf', type='vcf', hg='hg38',
                      sampleName='NA12878')

Keyword arguments
-----------------
  file        str   Path to BAM / VCF / bgzip+tabix VCF  (required)
  type        str   'bam' | 'vcf' | 'tbi'                (required)
  hg          str   'hg19' | 'hg38'  (auto-detected if omitted)
  baq         int   Base quality threshold (default 30, BAM only)
  maq         int   Mapping quality threshold (default 20, BAM only)
  noise       float Noise threshold (default 0.05, BAM only)
  sex         bool  Include sex-chromosome marker bits (default False)
  ucn         int   Unknown/complex notation flag (default 0)
  ref         int   Fill missing sex markers from reference (default 0)
  sampleName  str   Sample column name in multi-sample VCF/TBI
  minDepth    int   Minimum read depth (default 10, BAM only)

Bit layout
----------
  MADIB (6 bits)  +  AMB (58 bits)  +  SMB (2 bits)  +
  GVB (6 bits)  [+  XMB (48 bits, only when sex=True)]

  Total: 72 bits (12 base64 chars) without sex
         120 bits (20 base64 chars) with sex

RUNNING PYTHON TESTS

    python3 -m pytest tests/test_genomeid.py -v


